JSW Steel, Reliance, Unitech: India Stocks Preview

-- B y   M a l a v i k a   S h a r m a   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-03-08T03:34:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/dlf-jsw-steel-reliance-unitech-nestle-india-stocks-preview.html
(Corrects to remove north  India  reference in Chennai
Petroleum item.)  The following companies may have
unusual price changes in India trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
263.78, or 1.4 percent, to 18,222.67. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on
the National Stock Exchange declined 1.4 percent to 5,463.15.
The BSE 200 Index decreased 1.3 percent to 2,236.09. SGX S&P CNX
Nifty Index futures for March delivery dropped 0.4 percent to
5,461 at 10:24 a.m. in  Singapore .  Chennai Petroleum Corporation Ltd. (MRL IN): The unit of
the nation’s biggest refiner, Indian Oil Corp. will invest 123
billion rupees ($2.74 billion) in the next five years to expand
its refinery in Manali to 17 million tons a year from 10.5
million tons a year, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing
Finance Director N.C. Sridharan. The company’s shares fell 0.8
percent to 190.95 rupees.    DLF Ltd. (DLFU)  : India’s biggest developer was raised to
“hold” from “reduce” by Sandeep Mathew and Avneesh Sukhija,
analysts at BNP Paribas SA, who wrote in a note to investors
that recovery in the company’s office markets appears to be “on
track.” The company’s price estimate was lowered to 242 rupees
from 295 rupees because of a lack of new residential projects,
according to the report. The shares decreased 1.8 percent to
218.5 rupees.        JSW Steel Ltd. (JSTL)  : The nation’s third-biggest
manufacturer of the alloy reported an 8 percent increase in
steel production in February from a year earlier, according to
its statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange. The shares fell 3.5
percent to 919.65 rupees.    Nestle India Ltd. (NEST)  : The unit of the world’s
largest food company was lowered to “neutral” from “buy” at  UBS AG. (UBSN)  The brokerage raised the price estimate to 4,200 rupees
a shares from 3,750 rupees. The shares climbed 2.1 percent to
3,748.75 rupees.        PTC India Ltd. (PTCIN)  : India’s biggest power trader
agreed to purchase 100 megawatts of electricity on a longterm
basis from Torrent Power Ltd., according to an e-mailed
statement yesterday.  Separately, its PTC India Financial Services Ltd. plans to
raise about 4.5 billion rupees in an initial share sale and 1
billion rupees selling infrastructure bonds, Chairman Tantra Narayan Thakur said in Mumbai yesterday.  PTC India’s shares fell 1.4 percent to 89.5 rupees.    Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd. (RBXY)  : India’s biggest
drugmaker’s price estimate was cut to 630 rupees a share from
720 rupees a share at UBS, while the rating was unchanged at
“buy”. The stock fell 1.4 percent to 445.8 rupees.    Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL)  : The price estimate of
the nation’s most valuable company was cut to 1,120 rupees from
1,184 rupees a share at Citigroup Inc., while the “buy” rating
was maintained. The shares slid 0.5 percent to 977.05 rupees.    Unitech Ltd. (UT)  : India’s second-biggest developer’s
rating was raised to “buy” from “hold” at BNP Paribas’s
Mathew and Sukhija, who cited the view in a note to investors
that the company’s telecom risk is “minimal.” The shares
dropped 2.9 percent to 35.45 rupees.    UTV Software Communications Ltd. (UTV)  : The media
company backed by Walt Disney Co. may sell its 56 percent stake
in Indiagames for as much as 2.4 billion rupees to a U.S.
company or a venture capital fund, the Economic Times reported,
citing an official it didn’t identify. The shares rose 2 percent
to 535.6 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
